itools 0.62.8 (2011/05/24)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.i18n             itools.srx
  itools.core             itools.ical             itools.stl
  itools.csv              itools.log              itools.tmx
  itools.database         itools.loop             itools.uri
  itools.datatypes        itools.odf              itools.web
  itools.fs               itools.office           itools.workflow
  itools.gettext          itools.pdf              itools.xliff
  itools.git              itools.pkg              itools.xml
  itools.handlers         itools.python           itools.xmlfile
  itools.html             itools.relaxng
  itools.http             itools.rss

The itools.rest package has been removed.

There has been an small change to the API.  The 'utc' singleton from
itools.core has been replaced by the 'fixed_offset' factory. This is
how to update the code:

  Before                         Now
  -----------------------------  ------------------------------------
  from itools.core import utc    from itools.core import fixed_offset
                                 utc = fixed_offset(0)

Bugs fixed include:

   #970 traceback if writing on read-only ikaaro
  #1099 Image thumbnails can now fit the thumbnail size by cropping
  #1144 Method get_canonical_uri does not return a canonical uri
  #1179 Indexing Tokens do not do what is expected
  #1188 Prevent a traceback with a deepcopy of FixedOffset
  #1190 Build AndQuery and OrQuery step by step
  #1200 Workaround to Python bug http://bugs.python.org/issue11104


